206
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:17,034
"Medouze, your old father
will die soon,"

207
00:20:17,171 --> 00:20:20,140
"without ever understanding
what happened..."

208
00:20:20,274 --> 00:20:24,335
"when the whites
landed here."

209
00:20:24,478 --> 00:20:28,812
The old black also added:

210
00:20:28,949 --> 00:20:31,042
"I had a big brother,
Ousmane,"

211
00:20:31,185 --> 00:20:33,278
a little sister, Sokhna."

212
00:20:33,420 --> 00:20:36,116
"The white men hunted us."

213
00:20:36,256 --> 00:20:38,816
"They caught us
with lassos."

214
00:20:38,959 --> 00:20:45,626
"Then... after many days,
journey through the bush,"

215
00:20:45,766 --> 00:20:48,633
"They took us to the edge
of the big water."

216
00:20:48,769 --> 00:20:53,297
"One day, we were
unloaded here."

217
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:58,173
"We were sold to cut cane
for the whites."

218
00:21:01,982 --> 00:21:06,009
"I was a young boy like you,
Medouze."

219
00:21:06,153 --> 00:21:10,783
"All the blacks came down
from the hills with sticks,"

220
00:21:10,924 --> 00:21:14,223
"machetes, guns and torches."

221
00:21:14,361 --> 00:21:17,728
"They invaded the town
of St. Pierre."

222
00:21:17,865 --> 00:21:21,961
"They burned all the homes."

223
00:21:22,102 --> 00:21:26,903
"For the first time, blacks saw
whites shake with fear,"

224
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:29,941
